{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Encoder-Decoder Means"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An encoder-decoder model has two stacks. The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " reads the entire input with bidirectional self-attention, producing a rich representation of it. The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " then generates output tokens auto-regressively, attending to its own past outputs (causal self-attention) "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "and"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to the encoder's representation via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cross-attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". This is the original \"Attention is All You Need\" architecture, and it remains the natural fit for tasks that transform one sequence into another: translation, summarization, question answering."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Left: encoder (bidirectional) produces representations, cross-attention arrows feed them to the decoder (causal), which generates output tokens. T5 span corruption pre-training. Right: five NLP tasks reformatted as text-to-text: translation, summarization, classification, QA, regression."}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Attention: The Bridge"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each decoder block has three sub-layers, not two:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Masked self-attention:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " causal attention over previously generated output tokens."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-attention:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " queries come from the decoder's hidden state; keys and values come from the encoder's final representations. This is how the decoder \"reads\" the source."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feed-forward network:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " position-wise transformation."}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{CrossAttn}(Q, K, V) = \\text{softmax}\\!\\left(\\frac{QK^\\top}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V, \\quad Q = W_Q h^\\text{dec},\\ K = W_K h^\\text{enc},\\ V = W_V h^\\text{enc}"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "T5: Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "T5 (Raffel et al., 2020) uses a pure encoder-decoder architecture and reformulates "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "every NLP task as text-to-text"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Classification, regression, translation, QA — all are handled by the same model trained with the same cross-entropy loss and the same greedy/beam decoding."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The key idea is a simple prefix that tells the model which task to perform:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "translate English to French: The house is wonderful.\n→ La maison est merveilleuse.\n\nsummarize: Scientists discovered a new species of deep-sea fish...\n→ Researchers found a new deep-sea fish.\n\nmnli hypothesis: The cat is outside. premise: The cat sat on the mat.\n→ entailment\n\nstsb sentence1: Cats are small. sentence2: Cats are tiny.\n→ 4.2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pre-Training: Span Corruption"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "T5 is pre-trained with a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "span corruption"}, {"type": "text", "text": " objective. Random contiguous spans (average length 3 tokens) are selected to cover 15% of input tokens, each replaced by a unique sentinel token "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<X>"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<Y>"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", etc. The decoder is trained to output the original spans labeled by their sentinels:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Original:        \"The cat sat on the old mat\"\nEncoder input:   \"The <X> on <Y> mat\"\nDecoder target:  \"<X> cat sat <Y> old </s>\""}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compared to BERT's token-level masking, span corruption exercises the decoder's generation capability and reduces the proportion of \"easy\" tokens the model must predict."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using T5 with HuggingFace"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import T5Tokenizer, T5ForConditionalGeneration\n\ntokenizer = T5Tokenizer.from_pretrained(\"t5-small\")\nmodel = T5ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(\"t5-small\")\n\n# Translation\ninput_ids = tokenizer(\n    \"translate English to German: The cat sat on the mat.\",\n    return_tensors=\"pt\",\n).input_ids\n\noutput_ids = model.generate(input_ids, max_new_tokens=50)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))\n# \"Die Katze saß auf der Matte.\""}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Summarization with Flan-T5 (instruction-tuned)\nfrom transformers import pipeline\n\nsummarizer = pipeline(\"summarization\", model=\"google/flan-t5-base\")\nresult = summarizer(\n    \"summarize: Machine learning is a field of inquiry devoted to understanding \"\n    \"and building methods that 'learn' — that is, methods that leverage data to \"\n    \"improve performance on some set of tasks.\",\n    max_new_tokens=60,\n)\nprint(result[0][\"summary_text\"])\n# \"Machine learning is a method of data analysis that automates analytical model building.\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Beam Search Decoding"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unlike decoder-only chat models that use sampling, encoder-decoder models for structured tasks typically use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "beam search"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": maintain the top-"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "k"}, {"type": "text", "text": " candidate sequences at each step. This is because translation and summarization benefit from deterministic, high-quality outputs rather than diverse sampling."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "output_ids = model.generate(\n    input_ids,\n    num_beams=4,           # beam search with 4 beams\n    no_repeat_ngram_size=2,  # prevent repeating 2-grams\n    early_stopping=True,\n    max_new_tokens=100,\n)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0], skip_special_tokens=True))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing the Right Architecture"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strengths"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical tasks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-only (BERT)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full bidirectional context; compact"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classification, NER, embeddings, extractive QA"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only (GPT)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scales to very large; strong few-shot"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Open-ended generation, chat, code, reasoning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-decoder (T5)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Source context fully available to decoder; unified task format"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Translation, summarization, structured QA, multi-task"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The line between decoder-only and encoder-decoder has blurred at scale. Large decoder-only models (GPT-4, Claude, Llama) handle translation and summarization well via in-context learning. Encoder-decoder models still hold an efficiency edge for constrained, sequence-to-sequence tasks where the source length is bounded."}]}]}]}}